## GUARDRAIL 10 — Pre-Output Self-Verification Checklist

Before finalizing ANY template or style output:

- [ ] Every shortcut appears in the Closed Shortcut Registry (Guardrail 1)
- [ ] No shortcut appears alongside its own expansion (N-1, Guardrail 2)
- [ ] No `flex` prefix before a flex shortcut (N-2, Guardrail 3)
- [ ] No Tailwind palette color (`text-red-*`, `bg-blue-*`, `text-gray-*`)
- [ ] No `bg-white`, `bg-black`, `text-white`, `text-black`
- [ ] No `rem` / `em` in sizing classes, style blocks, or arbitrary values
- [ ] Unit priority respected for raw sizing: `vw/vh > % > px`
- [ ] No raw z-index class — only 6 semantic tokens
- [ ] No element has > 7 raw utility classes for a structural pattern (Rule of 7)
- [ ] `glass-base` not used directly — use `glass-panel`, `glass-capsule`, `glass-shell`, `glass-card`, or `glass-icon-box`
- [ ] `duration-300` / `duration-200` not present — use named duration tokens

